						<summary>

						<p>Vijayanagara, Dēvarāya-Mahārāya, Viśvāvasu, Māsi 10 = A.D. 1426, February 4.</p>						

						<p>End portion mutilated. Seems to record gift of a <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> of land to the temple by Āvuḍaiya-nāyaṉār Āṇḍapiḷḷai Villavarāyar, the arasu of Peruṅgōḷiyūr, in connection with the asylum <hi rend="italic">(āśrayam)</hi> he entered with the nāḍu of Iraṇḍumalai-nāḍu.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 701.]</p>						

